name: Bostik Cementone Plasterers Primer 10L
description: Bostik Cementone Plasterer's primer is specially designed for the plastering professionals. Surfaces are prepared by priming and stabilizing and is excellent for skim coats. This product can be applied to a porous or non-porous substrate. It is made to stabilise well-adhered emulsion paint, wallpaper adhesive residues, old plaster/render surfaces to provide a super clean finish. This product also acts as a waterproofer for walls when plastered or boarded over. The solution should always be stored and transported in an upright position with the lid secured and must be stored at temperatures between 5 degree Celsius and 35 degree Celsius to ensure effectiveness. name: Blue Circle Mastercrete Cement 25kg Plastic Bag
description: Blue Circle Mastercrete Cement is a superior Portland-limestone general purpose cement that contains a number of additives to increase the performance, creating a superior product. Mastercrete entrains a controlled quality of air and the addition of admixture of the air-entraining type is unnecessary and not recommended for concrete.In mortar and rendering, the addition of proprietary air-entraining mortar plasticiser is either unnecessary or the manufacturer’s recommended dosage significantly reduced dependant upon the sand used.Other proprietary admixtures of the non air-entraining type and pigments are compatible with Mastercrete. Trial mixes are recommended to determine optimum mix proportions. Features & Benefits:   Multi-application - Ideal for use in use in concrete, bricklaying, floor screed & render.  Improved resistance to freeze/thaw attack - Compared to traditional cement.  Improved workability - Its cohesive mix is less likely to segregate and offers an improved trowel feel.  Reduced water demand - In concrete mortar and screeds for a more durable end product.  The original weatherproof packaging - Supplied in recyclable hard wearing, tear-proof packaging that was designed for external storage prior to use.

name: Bostik Cementone Cement Colourant Black 1kg
description: Bostik Cementone Cement Colourant Black 1kg is specifically formulated to colour cement, concrete, renders, mortars and screeds. Cementone Colours for Cement use pigments that conform to BS EN 12878:2005. Cementone Colours for Cement is a light-fast and disperse easily into the dry mix. When used as recommended Cementone Colours do not affect the final mix. Cementone Colours are suitable for interior and exterior use and are inter-mixable to give a wide range of shades.Key featuresDisperses easily in dry mixDoes not impair performance of mixAvailable in range of coloursApplicationGauge colour by weight, not by volume. In normal use a good depth of colour will be achieved by ratio 1 part Cementone Colours for Cement to 20 parts cement by weight e.g. 1.25Kg Colour to 25Kg cement. For lighter shades reduces the weight of Cementone Colours for cement. For darker shades increase the weight of Cementone Colours for cement. The ratio should never exceed 1 part Cementone Colours for cement to 10 parts cement by weight e.g. 2.5Kg Cementone Colours for cement to 25Kg cement. Always use product from the same batch, the exact colour achieved will depend on the grade and colour of sand, cement and aggregate used. To ensure colour consistency use the same grades and weights of ingredients for the whole project. The same quantity of gauging water must be added to each batch. For pastel shades white cement is recommended. When colour matching, always assess match on a set, dry mix. Add Cementone Colours for cement direct to the dry cement. name: Dryrod Damp Proofing Rods (10 Pack) - Next Generation Rising Damp Treatment from The Makers of Dryzone
description:
Dryrods Deliver the Correct Dose Every Time
Traditional rising damp treatment methods utilise cream or liquid injection. These methods can be prone to operator error leading to under-treatment and DPC failure. Due to their unique patented design, Dryrod Damp-Proofing Rods deliver the correct dose of active ingredient every time.
Extensively Tested and Internationally Approved
Laboratory testing has proven that Dryrod Damp-Proofing Rods out-perform competing treatment methods, even in highly-saturated walls and freezing temperatures. They have also been approved by the British Board of Agrement and the German WTA organization.
100% Active Ingredient for Maximum Water Repellency
It is not possible to infuse 100% pure active ingredient into a traditional Damp-Proofing Cream. Thanks to their unique fibre rods, Dryrod Damp-Proofing Rods are saturated with 100% silane/siloxane. Only the pure active ingredient diffuses into the wall, in a controlled dose that ensures consistent application. Cheaper creams may seem more attractive, but they often only contain around 25%-50% active ingredient. They cannot out-perform Dryrod.Guarantee - StatutoryFeatures and benefitsDryrod Damp-Proofing Rods are patented fibre rods that carry a powerful water-repellent material. They are simply inserted into holes drilled at regular intervals along a mortar course. Once inserted, the rods diffuse their water-repellent material along the mortar course, curing to form an effective barrier to rising damp.

They have been scientifically proven to eliminate rising damp even in highly-saturated walls. This performance has also been internationally tested and approved.Dryrod Damp-Proofing Rods Next Generation DPC - The most effective form of damp proofing for walls; outperforms creams, gels or liquids.Fast & Simple to Install DIY rising damp treatment. Less messy than older traditional damp course injection creams or liquidsNo specialist equipment required - simply insert into 12mm holes in the mortar lines of a building to form a powerful waterproof barrierExact Dosage - Delivers the correct dose every time eliminating guesswork.BBA Approved – The High-Performance DPC Treatment is Certified by the British Board of Agrément to be effective against the ingress of moisture for at least 20 years

Used with Gypframe GL8 tracks, they create a cost-effective, virtually independent metal wall-lining system where an external wall or substrate is quite uneven or out of plumb.It won't twist or warp and is up to 45% quicker to install than traditional timber.These metals are up to 50% lighter than equivalent timber systems and 70% lighter than blockwork.The patented ultrasteel process lends greater strength to the component and makes fixing easier; thereby. improving screw retention and pull-out by up to 20%.
